{"id": "EUVD-2022-55640", "enisaUuid": "a9ea648a-a59b-3d9f-be27-ace270b0afd3", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nbrcmfmac: return error when getting invalid max_flowrings from dongle\n\nWhen firmware hit trap at initialization, host will read abnormal\nmax_flowrings number from dongle, and it will cause kernel panic when\ndoing iowrite to initialize dongle ring.\nTo detect this error at early stage, we directly return error when getting\ninvalid max_flowrings(>256).", "datePublished": "2025-09-17T14:56:10", "dateUpdated": "2025-12-23T13:29:02", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/3cc9299036bdb647408e11e41de3eb1ff6d428cd", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/2e8bb402b060a6c22160de3d72cee057698177c8", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/10c4b63d09a5b0ebf1b61af1dae7f25555cf58b6", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/87f126b25fa8562196f0f4c0aa46a446026199bf", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/200347eb3b2608cc8b54c13dd1d5e03809ba2eb2", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/2aca4f3734bd717e04943ddf340d49ab62299a00", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2022-50358"], "aliases": ["CVE-2022-50358"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.03, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "05cc3ced-dd1b-33f8-9a8c-7e7676f9921f", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "1da177e4c3f41524e886b7f1b8a0c1fc7321cac2 <2e8bb402b060a6c22160de3d72cee057698177c8"}, {"id": "0e786c60-089f-33cb-b664-20783f1c892e", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.10.163"}, {"id": "1a295635-bdb8-3a1a-9090-77cf5d7ddf9d", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "9e37f045d5e7f33450515f237c2f6f6bfee137dd <2e8bb402b060a6c22160de3d72cee057698177c8"}, {"id": "21383449-5a7c-30e3-83e1-490c64910d80", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "1da177e4c3f41524e886b7f1b8a0c1fc7321cac2 <87f126b25fa8562196f0f4c0aa46a446026199bf"}, {"id": "2b8ab0fe-5a60-3013-983b-c5ac3a5a8d4b", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "1da177e4